{"title":"Denoising Time Cycle Modeling for Recommendation","domain":"IR_REC","seeds":[{"problem":"User behavior histories contain many interactions irrelevant to a given target item, which act as noise and degrade time-cycle modeling and CTR prediction.","method":"Introduce a gated filter unit that measures relevance between the target item embedding and each behavior’s item embedding via a cosine-based score, then applies a thresholded, piece-wise gating to produce weights f_k, setting irrelevant behaviors to zero. This denoised sequence is then used for time-cycle modeling, ensuring only target-related behaviors contribute. (Supported: gated filter unit with cos activation and threshold; zeroing out noise behaviors.)"},{"problem":"Discrete semantic time features (e.g., hour, weekday, month) break temporal continuity, hindering learning of absolute time cycle patterns (ATC).","method":"Propose an absolute time convolution module that aggregates surrounding time-slot embeddings at multiple granularities. It performs 1D convolution with ReLU over a window (j=0..J, default J=2) of neighboring time slots followed by max-pooling, then concatenates across granularities to form Λ(t). This preserves local continuity and captures absolute cyclic patterns. (Supported: surrounding time embeddings, conv+pooling, multi-granularity, diminishing impact with larger j.)"},{"problem":"Modeling relative time cycles (RTC)—how influence decays or repeats over time intervals—and fusing them with absolute cycles is crucial for timely recommendation.","method":"Learn a continuous, translation-invariant temporal embedding Φ(t) inspired by Bochner’s theorem, with trainable frequency parameters, so that the inner product ⟨Φ(t1),Φ(t2)⟩ depends only on the interval |t2−t1|. Combine this RTC representation with the ATC Λ(t) and apply a time cycle attention over the denoised behavior sequence to extract cycle patterns relevant to the target; concatenate with a user-interest module and predict CTR via an MLP. This fusion yields consistent gains over strong baselines on four datasets. (Supported: translation-invariant kernel via Bochner, trainable ω, time cycle attention combining Λ and Φ, concatenation with user-interest module, improved results across datasets.)"}]}
